race.comment: DIRECT FIRE (1) has contested three Midways this prep and been competitive without threatening, the latest over 1400m at Rosehill when he was there on the bend but tired. Down in class and draws a lovely gate. Ready to peak at the fourth run back. The promising KING NIC (2) is the danger. Continued his excellent form this prep with a tough win over 1400m at this track three weeks ago. Strong through the line that day so an extra 100m looks ideal. Seven-year-old ALL MACHIAVELLIAN (3) lines up at Kembla for the 27th time. His last two here over the mile have been excellent efforts, racing on pace one day and ridden cold the other. As good as any of these on his day. PRETTY SASSY (6) gave away a massive start and worked home well over 1400m here recently. In the mix if she stays in touch. The chances look to end there, with BOBS BACK (5) one to throw in wider exotics.
